# Execute

![N|Solid](http://www.alex-arriaga.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Console-128.png)

To install, deploy and run ionic

**run** (sudo if required, you need npm to install ionic and bower to this course ):

```sh
$ npm install -g grunt-cli
$ npm install cordova ionic -g
```

Create a new proyect (name) with template , e.g:

```sh
$ ionic start conFusion sidemenu
```

To serve app

```sh
$  ionic serve
```

To install json-server

```sh
$ npm install json-server -g
```

Run

```sh
$ json-server --watch db.json
```
Serve new content in "public" folder (create if does not exist).

